               </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text based on autopsy</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Gaius Haterius Agatocles, freedman of Gaius</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#AA">
                <p>Although the identity of this Agatocles and his former owner as unknown to us, there is another Haterius known to us in Sicily: a M. Haterius Candidus who was proconsul of Sicily in the Neronian period, as attested in Agrigento, see <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000473">ISic000473</ref>. The name Agatocles is relatively uncommon, appearing in Latin only in a handful of other dedications, often (but not always) in the context of freedpersons (as in the case of our Agatocles here).</p>
            </div>
